                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3743: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-01T00:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1922—midnight</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received March 3, 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Department’s 42, February 21, 3 p.m. Yen<note n="62" xml:id="d582fn62">W. W.
                        Yen, Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs.</note> informed orally and in
                    writing, stated orally today no possibility of obtaining any funds during the
                    present Cabinet crisis. He seemed very disheartened over financial and political
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
